        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairmont, or 11 miles southwest of Lumberton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lumberton, Fairmont, Boardman, Howellsville, Butters, Hestertown,
Smiths, Barker Ten Mile, Proctorville, Mcdonald, Orrum, Raynham, and
Southeastern Regional Medical Center.

This includes Interstate 95 in North Carolina between mile markers 4
and 21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
